</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,1814,1877]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[189,525,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ameroglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manoelfelixii">
<emphasis box="[189,525,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ameroglossum manoelfelixii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs exclusively on granite outcrops in 
<collectingRegion box="[1038,1198,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Paraíba State</collectingRegion>
, restricted to the Agreste da Borborema, Curimataú and Brejo microregions. Elevation between 500 and 
<specimenCount box="[1218,1300,1850,1876]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1218,1295,1850,1876]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
